**What feature/behavior/change do you want?**
When you try to create a cluster in an AWS Region that has one or more local zones enabled, and you are also creating the VPC as part of the cluster creation process, then eksctl passes the subnets in a local zone to the cluster. Unlike regional subnets, EKS can't place network interfaces into Local Zone subnets. As a result, the cluster creation process fails.

**Why do you want this feature?**
AWS customers are trying to use local zones in EKS clusters and are trying to create EKS clusters that include worker nodes in local zones. Currently, they have to create the VPC with regional and local zone subnets as a separate step and then explicitly specify only regional subnets in their configuration file while creating an EKS cluster. They would like to do this with a one step process.
